# addEntry(_:)

**Instance Method**

Adds a new entry to the end of the receiver and gives it the specified title.

## Declaration

```swift
@MainActor func addEntry(_ title: String) -> NSFormCell
```

## Parameters

- **title**: The title for the new form entry.

## Return Value

The form cell object that was created for the entry.

## Discussion

The new entry has no tag, target, or action, but is enabled and editable.

## Related Documentation

- **action**: Returns the receiver’s action-message selector.
- **target**: Returns the receiver’s target object.
- **isEnabled**: A Boolean value indicating whether the cell is currently enabled.
- **isEditable**: A Boolean value indicating whether the cell is editable.
- **tag**: Returns the receiver’s tag.
- **Form Programming Topics**
- **Matrix Programming Guide**

## Adding and Removing Entries

- **insertEntry(_:at:)**: Inserts an entry with the specified title into the receiver.
- **removeEntry(at:)**: Removes and releases the entry at the specified index.
